---
title: Firecracker Beef Lo Mein with Green Beans
description: **Now with leaner ground beef and more rice! You asked, we listened: This isn't the HelloFresh you remember. Bigger menu. Upgraded recipes. Increased portion sizes. More variety. The best way to cook dinner just got BETTER.**

This speedy stir-fry features savory ground beef, crisp green beans, and scallions—all tossed with lo mein noodles in a bold soy chili sauce. It’s finished with a drizzle of sweet and spicy firecracker sauce and a sprinkle of scallion greens for a satisfying meal that’s ready in minutes.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/686d39f38d751c3919190d61-49c505bc.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/686d39f38d751c3919190d61-en-US.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: East Asia
course: main course
time required: 20 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 810 kcal
  fat: 40 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 74 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 2170 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/firecracker-beef-lo-mein-686d39f38d751c3919190d61
servings: 2
---

Bring a #medium pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary; cut crosswise into 2-inch-long pieces. Trim @scallions{2}; cut whites into 1-inch pieces and thinly slice greens. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, half the @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{2%ounce} (you'll use the rest later), and as much @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like.

Set aside until ready to use.

Once water is boiling, add @Lo Mein Noodles{4.5%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Drain and set aside.

While noodles cook, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, green beans, scallion whites, ginger, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until beef is cooked through and veggies are tender, ~{4-6%minutes}. (For 4 servings, you may need to work in batches.)

Drain any excess grease from pan (or use a #paper towel{} and #tongs{} to sop it up!).

Add @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, remaining chili sauce, and @water{1/4%cup} to pan with beef and green beans; continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce is warmed through, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Remove from heat.

To pan with beef and green beans, add drained noodles and @butter{1/2%tbsp}. Toss to combine; taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide lo mein between shallow bowls. Drizzle with as much firecracker sauce as you like. Top with scallion greens and serve.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.